{"flatpakAppId":"io.github.evilsocket.opensnitch","name":"OpenSnitch","summary":"GNU/Linux interactive application firewall","description":"\n    <p>\n      Whenever a program tries to establish a new connection, it'll prompt the user to allow or deny it.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      The user can decide if block the outgoing connection based on properties of the connection: by port, by uid, by\ndst ip, by program or a combination of them. These rules can last forever, until the app restart or just one time.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      The GUI allows the user to view live outgoing connections, as well as search by process, user, host or port.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      OpenSnitch can also work as a system-wide domains blocker, by using lists of domains, list of IPs or list of regular\nexpressions.\n    </p>\n  ","developerName":null,"projectLicense":"GPL-3.0-or-later","homepageUrl":"https://github.com/evilsocket/opensnitch","donationUrl":null,"translateUrl":null,"bugtrackerUrl":"https://github.com/evilsocket/opensnitch/issues","helpUrl":"https://github.com/evilsocket/opensnitch/wiki","categories":[{"name":"System"},{"name":"Security"},{"name":"Monitor"},{"name":"Network"}],"downloadFlatpakRefUrl":"python3-opensnitch-ui","currentReleaseVersion":null,"currentReleaseDescription":null,"iconDesktopUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble-security/io/github/evilsocket.opensnitch/d8490d893271eeef48dffbcff328d1fe/icons/128x128/python3-opensnitch-ui_opensnitch-ui.png","iconMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble-security/io/github/evilsocket.opensnitch/d8490d893271eeef48dffbcff328d1fe/icons/128x128/python3-opensnitch-ui_opensnitch-ui.png","screenshots":[{"thumbUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble-security/io/github/evilsocket.opensnitch/d8490d893271eeef48dffbcff328d1fe/screenshots/image-1_224x95.png","imgMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble-security/io/github/evilsocket.opensnitch/d8490d893271eeef48dffbcff328d1fe/screenshots/image-1_752x